<P>
   TRAVEL-SOUTH _ Southern Happenings. (Thrasher, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DAYTON-DUNBAR _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Lack of access to health care
``isn't so much racial today as it is economic, but it's still a
problem in the black community,'' said LaVerne Sci, historic site
manager of the Dunbar House State Memorial Museum. Sci said Dunbar
would be proud that the museum is hosting the Sixth Annual West
Dayton Diabetes Day on Thursday. (DeBrosse, Dayton Daily News)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LEGO-ROBOTS _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Lego Mindstorms, the latest Lego
product, is not the toy you remember from childhood. With
Mindstorms, you get to build and program your own robot. (Chan
Santos, Austin American Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SLAVEMASTER _ LONGVIEW, Texas _ Defying political correctness,
descendants of Panola County, Texas, slaves are dedicating a
historical marker to the slavemaster who brought their families
here. ``It's weird that black people would want to do a marker on a
slavemaster,'' admitted Barbara Jefferson-Bonner, a Panola County
historian specializing in black history. ``Slavemasters are
supposed to be mean and cruel, but he wasn't that way.'' The marker
will be dedicated for Spearman ``Major'' Holland, who brought
Bonner's family here as slaves in the 1840s. (Jacobs, Longview News
Journal) MOVED.
</P>
