A3251 &Cx1f; tad-z
u i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BRITAIN-CHARLES-1111-     11-10 0477
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BRITAIN-CHARLES-1111-1STLD-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    EDs: in 3rd graf, corrects to read 'He got on very well. He was
very . . . '
 &HT;    PRINCE CHARLES, 'THE EVERYMAN,' GOES HI-TECH LAUNCHING WEB SITE
 &HT;    Moving in both the (i) International and (l) Lifestyle
categories.
 &HT;    By BERT ROUGHTON JR. 
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON _ The heir to the throne of Henry the VIII fired up his
Web site Tuesday, inviting Web surfers from across the realm -- and
beyond -- to e-mail their future sovereign.
</P>
<P>
   Prince Charles, who turns 50 this week, was shown on television
here studiously manipulating a laptop as he surfed the site at
www.princeofwales.gov.uk. Buckingham Palace clearly wanted to
portray the prince as thoroughly a man of his times.
</P>
<P>
   ``He got on very well. He was very interested to see the site
put together according to the specifications of himself and his
office,'' said Nicole Davenport, the Internet site's designer. ``He
enjoyed very much particularly the biographical section, the speech
section -- also the section about his work. He got along absolutely
fine with it, and he very much enjoyed surfing around having a look
to see what the site said.''
</P>
<P>
   The site describes the prince's life and times in 354 Web pages
with 250 photographs. His major speeches dating back to 1968 are
reproduced in full.
</P>
<P>
   But if you're looking for the latest lurid gossip about the
royals, you're clicking up the wrong page. Charles' site contains
dispassionate accounts of the prince's life, including his
relationship with the late Princess Diana. Their separation and
divorce is reported in an unadorned passage in the biographical
section.
</P>
<P>
   ``The marriage was dissolved on August 28, 1996,'' it says.
``The princess was still regarded as a member of the royal
family.''
</P>
<P>
   In the next paragraph, the biography notes that ``the princess
was killed in a car crash in Paris.''
</P>
<P>
   His lover of 25 years, Camilla Parker Bowles, gets only a single
mention.
</P>
<P>
   The prince is not the first British Royal to have his own Web
site. Buckingham Palace launched its site 18 months ago, and
recorded more than 100 million hits in the first year. Also, there
are dozens of unofficial Web sites for Princess Diana; only
official one for her charity.
</P>
<P>
   The site's forum page on Tuesday listed five pages of responses
from surfers on topics such as the prince's concerns about
architecture, agriculture community regeneration and even religion.
Most of the messages, all of which were at least generally
supportive if not adoring of the prince, were from England, but
there also were a few from Canada and the United States.
</P>
<P>
   The prince, whose popularity has risen since Diana's death, will
review comments, and he might even respond to some of them himself.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-11-10-98 1556EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19981110.0114 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-10 15:56 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3252 &Cx1f; taf-z
u d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-WINE-TASTINGS-NYT &LR;      11-10 0131
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WINE-TASTINGS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WINE OF THE WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Chassagne-Montrachet Rouge, Jean-Noel Gagnard, 1996, Burgundy,
France. About $20.
</P>
<P>
   Great Burgundy for $20? No. Good Burgundy? Yes. And here is the
wine to prove it. Chassagne-Montrachet is generally thought of as
white wine country. With parts of the great Montrachet and
Batard-Montrachet vineyards within the Chassagne-Montrachet town
borders, it is easy to understand why.
</P>
<P>
   But in any good year, almost 60 percent of
Chassagne-Montrachet's wines are red. Their relative obscurity can
be a windfall for the Burgundy lover.
</P>
<P>
   This wine, for example, may lack the elegance of a fine Volnay,
but it has good body and can hold its own with some highly touted
Burgundies.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-11-10-98 1556EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19981110.0115 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-11-10 15:57 </DATE_TIME>
