<P>
   LOTT-SENATE (Washington) _ While House Republicans scrap over
leadership posts in the aftermath of the GOP's poor election
showing, there is no such blood-letting in the Senate. We explore
the reasons why Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott has escaped
unscathed. By JUDY HOLLAND.
