   COURT-AIRLINES (Washington) _ Was an El Al search of a woman's
luggage so intrusive and traumatic to her that she should be able
to sue the Israeli airline for $5 million for the mental anguish
she suffered? Or was her illness simply an accident stemming from a
routine check, an event that would bar her from big damages? The
Supreme Court hears arguments on those questions. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   SUPREME-COURT (Washington) _ A unanimous Supreme Court rejects a
Dallas-area inventor's bill to recover a patent, saying the Texan
waited too long after marketing his product to apply for the
protection. By STEVE LASH.
</P>
<P>
   GUN-CONTROL (Washington) _ Both the opponents and supporters of
gun control predict problems with new ``instant check'' for gun
buyers that goes into effect Dec. 30 under the federal Brady Act.
By JOHN DRAKE.
</P>
