   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HEART-RISK (Dallas) _ Beware the Monday nights of winter. Not
only do the risks of heart attack increase on Mondays and in the
winter, but a heart attack at night is more likely to kill than one
that occurs during the day, say researchers at the 71st scientific
sessions of the American Heart Association. By RUTH SoRELLE.
</P>
<P>
   WEB-INITIATIVE (San Francisco) _ A Silicon Valley venture
capitalist is asking Internet users to help craft a school-choice
ballot initiative and then sign it on-line, a test of cyberspace
democracy that may be ahead of its time. By JULIAN GUTHRIE.
</P>
<P>
   HOMELESS-POLICY (San Francisco) _ Homeless people who are
arrested repeatedly for public drunkenness would have to choose
between a detoxification program or jail under a new push to find a
solution to San Francisco's chronic vagrancy problem. But the
proposal quickly drew criticism from people who say the city is
trying to make homelessness a crime. By GREGORY LEWIS and RACHEL
GORDON.
</P>
