   INTERNATIONAL NEWS (``i'' cateogy)
</P>
<P>
   MITCH-WARNING (Undated) _ By causing horific death and
destruction high in the mountains of Central America, Hurricane
Mitch exploded the myth that tropical storms only cause damage
along the coast. The director of the National Hurricane Center in
Miami admits the warning system fell far short, especially for
Nicaragua, where a thousand people died. By ED HEGSTROM.
</P>
