CHICKS-MUSIC (Los Angeles) The Dixie Chicks _ Emily Erwin, Natalie
Maines and Martie Seidel _ are happening in a big way. Their
flawless three-part harmony-based sound is as contemporary as
anything out there, but with a genuine traditional streak. On Nov.
23, the trio will appear on TV with Dick Clark announcing the
American Music Awards nominees. By Fred Shuster. 
. 
HOCH-STAGE (Los Angeles) _ What screwed-up faces and convulsive
sobs were to the comedy of Lucille Ball, hip-hop culture is to the
comedy of Danny Hoch. Hoch brings his latest show, ``Jails,
Hospitals &AMP; Hip-Hop'' to The Actors Gang Nov. 11-Dec. 13, presented
jointly by Actors Gang and the Mark Taper Forum. By Reed Johnson. 
. 
HOLLYBOWL-MUSIC (Los Angeles) _ Making good on its new overseer's
pledge to bring more jazz and world beat music to L.A.'s best-known
performance venue, the Hollywood Bowl on Tuesday unveiled an
upcoming season that includes an expanded jazz series and a new
Sunday series featuring everything from Argentinean tango and
Armenian choral music to U.S. gospel and Native American dance
theater. By Reed Johnson. 
. 
TALKIN'-RADIO (Los Angeles) _ For professional photographer,
husband and dad Dan Wagner, Howard Stern's radio show became an
obsession he could only overcome by writing a book. Wagner's
``Getting to Howard: The Odyssey of an Obsessed Howard Stern Fan''
(Ilicium Books; $23.95), is a true-life account of an ultimate
Stern groupie. By Fred Shuster. 
. 

