<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ The mother walked nervously toward Gate 42
at Dallas/Fort Worth Airport, her eyes scanning the crowd for the
son she had not seen in 17 years. She had not held him in her arms
since he was a baby, and had had only sporadic contact with him
over the years. Hoping that a reunion would erase the emptiness she
felt, she'd hired a private investigator in Canada to contact the
boy and arrange a meeting. There he is, she thought, spotting a
teen who was looking her way. But as she drew closer, her heart
started racing. The boy turned out to be an imposter. By GABRIELLE
