<HEADLINE>
LINK BETWEEN HEART DISEASE, AMINO ACID YET TO BE DEFINED 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By RUTH SoRELLE 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ The link between homocysteine and heart disease has yet
to be defined, prompting experts Tuesday to advise against
screening the population for elevated levels of the amino acid or
vitamin treatments except in rare cases.
</P>
<P>
   Of 11 studies performed to define the link between homocysteine
_ an amino acid _ and development of cardiovascular disease, six
showed a correlation between high homocysteine levels and five did
not, said Dr. Ronald Krauss, immediate past president of the
American Heart Association's nutrition committee, which wrote the
advisory.
</P>
<P>
   ``Despite the fact that vitamin intake lowers the homocysteine
level, there |Pgw
</P>
