 Small-Business Resource Guide on the Web  &HT;       
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &LR;  &QL; 
 &LR; There are many Web sites to help entrepreneurs start and build a
business. Here are a few of them:
<P>
   _ &UR; Small Business Administration &LR; ,  &LR; www.sba.gov &LR; . U.S. Small
Business Administration's Web site has a section devoted to
starting a business. It includes a startup kit and information on
research, business plans, patents and trademarks, outside resources
and winning ideas.
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; SCORE &LR; ,  &LR; www.score.org &LR; . Service Corps of Retired Executives
offers free, confidential business counseling by e-mail as well as
other information, from financing your small business to dealing
with year 2000 computer problems.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; _ &UR; Yahoo Small Business &LR; ,  &LR; smallbusiness.yahoo.com &LR; . Yahoo, one
of the leading Internet search engines and Web portals, has
launched a comprehensive online resource that offers information
about all aspects of a small business plus news articles,
information on conferences and seminars, government agencies and
more.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;   &UR;  &LR; _ &UR; Quicken Small Business &LR; ,
 &LR; www.quicken.com/small &LR; (underscore) &LR; business &LR; . Extensive small
business site from Intuit, creator of the top-selling Quicken books
and financial software, features expert advice on starting a
business, marketing, finance and other issues.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; _ &UR; Netscape Netcenter &LR; ,  &LR; www.netscape.com/netcenter/ &LR; 
 &LR; smallbusiness/ &LR; . New, in-depth Web page on Netscape's Internet
portal site has news, features and other information for
small-business owners.
</P>
<P>
   _ &UR; Nolo Press &LR; ,  &LR; www.nolo.com &LR; . Berkeley publisher of self-help
legal books and software offers plenty of useful information on
starting and running a small business including legal guides and
forms.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; _ &UR; Business Owner's Toolkit &LR; ,  &LR; www.toolkit.cch.com &LR; . CCH Inc.,
a Chicago business information company, offers step-by-step
checklists, model business plans, forms, and other business
documents and advice.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; _ &UR; Working Solo &LR; ,  &LR; www.workingsolo.com &LR; . Name of Web site and
new book (Wiley, $14.95) by consultant and author Terri Lonier.
Information can help individuals figure whether they have the right
personality to start and run their own business. Working Solo is
designed specifically for home-based business owners, consultants
and other independent professionals and includes a guide to more
than 1,200 business resources. Free monthly e-mail newsletter
offers tips to entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; _ &UR; Entrepreneurial Parent &LR; ,  &LR; www.en-parent.com &LR; . Designed
specifically for entrepreneurial work-at-home parents, this new
site offers online coaching as well as articles and advice from
experts in business startup, marketing, finance and other
categories, plus list of books, video and audio resources.
</P>
</TEXT>
