<P>
   BOEING-TOOL (Seattle) _ Another tool has been found in the
rudder of a Boeing airplane, this time on a new 777 operated by
EgyptAir. The plane had been flying with a hammer in a ``critical''
part of the rudder since the place was delivered last year. The
16-ounce hammer, left in the rudder during assembly of the 777, was
found by airline mechanics during a recent inspection. By the time
it was discovered, it had already caused two small cracks inside
the rudder, apparently from bouncing around during flight.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   DUNNE-GOP (Washington) _ Rep. Jennifer Dunn spent her first full
day as a candidate for House majority leader calling everyone she
knows and asking for help. But should she win next week, suddenly
everyone she knows will be seeking aid from her. Dunn, R-Wash., is
seeking is the No. 2 post in the House, which brings with it
considerable power to influence national policy, a bully pulpit
from which to influence national politics, and a traditional role
for steering federal dollars and programs back home.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (Story has moved in the ``w'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-THIEL-COLUMN (Seattle) _ On the University of Washington
football team and its Husky football. Brock Huard is swearing and
fans are too. But the critics of Jim Lambright forget, even Don
James had a rough streak too, and it last 25 games.
</P>
