<HEADLINE>
WORLD NEWS IN BRIEF 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   EUROPE
</P>
<P>
   Britain: Pinochet'S Immunity Claim
</P>
<P>
   LONDON _ A lawyer for Gen. Augusto Pinochet told the highest
court in Britain that as a former head of state the general was
immune from prosecution for acts committed in his official
capacity. The 82-year-old Chilean general, who governed from 1973
to 1990, was arrested last month in London at the request of Spain,
which wants him extradited to face charges of crimes against
humanity. A lower court ruled that the arrest was illegal.
</P>
<P>
   ASIA
</P>
<P>
   India: Weak Trade With Pakistan
</P>
<P>
   India and Pakistan discussed their paltry bilateral trade but
made no substantive progress. The total trading was estimated at
$162.5 million in 1996-97, less than 1 percent of their global
trade.
</P>
</TEXT>
